{
  "text": "In the second proof in [CITATION_1] , Rachlin On the other hand, they proved their lemma by contradiction in two special cases in which perfect secrecy is not achievable for compressed sensing measurement. They derived that this measurement cannot satisfy perfect secrecy condition. So we presented a new theorem in which one of their counterexample is not included in message set.",
